{"key":"post-11761082","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11761082</id>\n<content>If it's a brand new bag, there may not be many contaminant spores on the vermiculite, since it's manufactured at very high temperature.&amp;nbsp; However, when the bag has been open for awhile, I've had non-treated verm develop cobweb mold many times, so I always spread it out on a cookie sheet and bake at 350F to 450F for at least half an hour.&amp;nbsp; Longer if it's a thicker layer.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>11760798</prev>\n<first>11760457</first>\n<last>11761082</last>\n<when>1262574948</when>\n<utime>01/04/10 05:15 AM</utime>\n</post>"}